docs.lead_paragraph: The Asia, with other interesting matter, brings us a fresh installment of the beauties of the New-York Correspondent of the London Times. He recurs to his favorite theme, the Whig celebration at Niagara Falls, which he again characterizes as a failure. Then comes the following exquisite specimen of ignorance,--in which a desire to pander to British prejudices, and a determination to vent his partizan malice, seem to strive for supremacy:

docs.lead_paragraph: WURTEMBERG.--The differences between the Government and the Chambers, on the subject of in creasing the estimates for the army, and which have al ready produced two or three dissolutions of the Legislature, were brought to a close on the 6th inst. The Government propositions were adopted, but with considerable modifications.

docs.lead_paragraph: It was once well said, that to send an uneducated child into the world is little better to him turn out into the streets a mad dog or a wild beast. According to the old fashioned creed of our fathers, mankind is constitutionally addicted to evil courses. He cannot help it, if, left to him self, he should chance to fall into unwholesome ways.

docs.lead_paragraph: The statues (by DAVID D'ANJERS,) of BERNARDIN DR ST. PIERRE, and CASSIMER DELAVIGNE, were inaugurated, at Havre, on Saturday last, with appropriate public ceremonies. M. DE VARENNES, French Minister at Berlin, has invited the Corps Diplomatique of that capital to attend "a divine service," which he purposes to have celebrated on the 15th, (to-morrow,) in honor of the anniversary of the Emperor.

headline.main: XXXIId CONGRESS....First Session.; SENATE. HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES.

docs.lead_paragraph: Mr. HUNTER moved that the Senate take up the Civil and Diplomatic Appropriation Bill. Mr. FISH appealed to the Senator to withdraw the motion, to enable him to move to take up BENNETT's Land Distribution Bill.
